First Choose Your Data

You can choose your x and y variable data sets on the control panel. Don't worry about which data set is the x variable and which is the y, the only thing that matters is the combination!

The data sets you select have the greatest impact on the accuracy of the classifier. Remember, this is the information your classifier will learn from. For best results, you should try to find a combination of data which creates the most separation between cancer positive and cancer negative patients.
